  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Rinse the Thai black rice and soak overnight in 2 1/4 cups of water. Pour the rice and the water it was soaking in into a rice cooker and add coconut milk and sugar. Stir everything together and turn on the rice cooker. Once cooked, set aside to cool."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "To make the mango dessert, combine the condensed milk, milk, and vanilla. Add a big scoop of sticky rice to 2 bowls, and top each bowl with a handful of shaved ice and diced mango. Pour the vanilla sauce over everything and top each bowl with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. You can also layer everything in a glass to make it a bit prettier."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "To make the blueberry dessert, combine the ice, milk, condensed milk, and vanilla in a blender and blend until smooth. Pour the mixture into two bowls. Add a scoop of sticky rice to each bowl, a scoop of blueberry ice cream (you can substitute vanilla ice cream, if you want), and a handful of blueberries."
    }
  ]
